<h2>Research</h2>
My research interests include geometric group theory, dynamical systems, and fractal geometry. See my <a href="CVMain.htm#PublicationsAndPreprints">my list of publications</a> or <a href="research.htm">my research page</a> for more information.

<h2>Teaching</h2>
This year I am teaching <a href="https://www.gla.ac.uk/coursecatalogue/course/?code=MATHS4112">4H/5E: Algebraic and Geometric Topology</a> (<a href="https://moodle.gla.ac.uk/course/view.php?id=33986">view on Moodle</a>) and <a href="https://www.gla.ac.uk/coursecatalogue/course/?code=MATHS2035">2F: Groups, Transformations, and Symmetries</a> (<a href="https://moodle.gla.ac.uk/course/view.php?id=33841">view on Moodle</a>).  See <a href="teaching.htm">my teaching page</a> for information on past courses I have taught.


<h2>About Me</h2>
<p>I received my PhD from <a href="https://math.cornell.edu/">Cornell University</a> in 2004, and I have previously served as a member of staff at Cornell University, at the <a href="https://www.st-andrews.ac.uk/">University of St&nbsp;Andrews</a> here in Scotland, at <a href="https://math.bard.edu/">Bard College</a> in upstate New York, and at <a href="https://www.math.tamu.edu/">Texas A&amp;M University</a>.  I have been at the University of Glasgow since August 2022.</p>


